BENCHMARK TESTS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
The benchmark suite verifies Tahoe's numerical correctness against
reference solutions.  Tests are organised into levels; each level has
its own README.md with the theme, subdirectory list, and status.

  level.0/README.md  — core capabilities
  level.1/README.md  — constitutive model verification
  level.2/README.md  — extended capabilities
  level.3/README.md  — MPI distributed-memory parallel
  level.4/README.md  — solver performance
  level.5/README.md  — modernised-solver benchmarks

This file documents the *running* and *comparison* mechanics that are
common to all levels.

BUILDING
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Build the project with CMake first. The `tahoe` solver and `compare`
tool are both built automatically:

  cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
  cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

  Executables: build/bin/tahoe   build/bin/compare


RUNNING TESTS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1 - Run simulations

  Point `tahoe` at any `run.batch` file. It will execute all XML
  input files in that branch of the tree:

  To run all level.0 tests (from the benchmark_XML/level.0 directory):

    cd benchmark_XML/level.0
    printf "run.batch\nquit\n" | ../../build/bin/tahoe

  To run a single test:

    cd benchmark_XML/level.0/2D.elastostatic
    printf "gravity.0.xml\nquit\n" | ../../../build/bin/tahoe

  Output files (*.run, *.geo, etc.) are written alongside the input
  XML files and are excluded from version control via .gitignore.

  For level.3 MPI tests, build with TAHOE_MPI=ON first, then:

    sudo apt-get install libopenmpi-dev   # system OpenMPI
    cmake -B build --fresh -DTAHOE_MPI=ON
    cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

    cd benchmark_XML/level.3/parallel
    /usr/bin/mpirun -np 4 ../../build/bin/tahoe -f run.batch

  IMPORTANT: use /usr/bin/mpirun (system OpenMPI), not the mpirun
  that conda may have placed earlier in your PATH (conda uses MPICH,
  which is ABI-incompatible with the system OpenMPI that Tahoe links
  against). See spoolesMPI/README.md for full troubleshooting notes.

  The automated script at the repo root handles all levels including
  level.3:

    ./run_benchmarks.sh           # all levels
    ./run_benchmarks.sh level.3   # level.3 only


Step 2 - Compare against benchmarks

  Run `compare` with the same batch file. Results are compared to the
  reference solutions stored in each local `benchmark/` sub-directory:

    cd benchmark_XML/level.0
    printf "run.batch\nquit\n" | ../../build/bin/compare

  A summary is written to `compare.summary` in the batch file's
  directory. Detailed per-variable differences appear on stdout.

  For level.3, `compare` is a serial tool run once per XML file after
  the MPI batch finishes. It reads the joined output files (*.io0.run,
  etc.) written by the parallel run and compares them against the
  reference files in each benchmark/ sub-directory:

    cd benchmark_XML/level.3/parallel
    /path/to/build/bin/compare -f elastostatic.xml
    /path/to/build/bin/compare -f elastostatic.N-LS.xml
    # ... (run_benchmarks.sh does this automatically)


PASS/FAIL CRITERIA
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Default absolute tolerance : 1.0e-10
  Default relative tolerance : 1.0e-8 (when rel_tol is specified)

Override globally on the command line:

    compare -abs_tol 2.5e-5

Override per-directory by placing a `compare.tol` file alongside the
`run.batch`:

    abs_tol 2.5e-5    # or rel_tol 1.0e-6 (disables abs_tol check)
    skip s12          # ignore variable "s12" in comparisons


KNOWN EXPECTED FAILURES (level.0–2)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
The 17 remaining failures across levels 0–2 are all real Tahoe code
regressions (not config drift); each is tracked under issue #37:

  bridging/             9 tests; BRIDGING_ELEMENT compiles cleanly but
                        crashes at runtime during atomistic-continuum
                        coupling init. Flag kept off in
                        ElementsConfig.h pending separate fix.
  adhesion/{2,3}.xml    2 tests; s11/s22 stresses differ from reference
                        by O(0.1) — adhesion element numerical regression.
  inputoutput/square    2 tests; output system fails to register the
                        configured I/O channels — no .io*.run produced.
  CSE.2.xml             1 test; bulk Q4 with nen=5 (phantom-node CSE)
                        unsupported by QuadT::EvaluateShapeFunctions.
  mat.{2.a,11.a}.xml    3 tests; small_strain_StVenant_DP_2D and
                        related material types not registered.

Overall pass rates (May 2026, default build; level.3 from MPI build):
  level.0  172 pass / 14 fail
  level.1  100 pass /  3 fail  (includes WLC + SuperLU benchmark)
  level.2   47 pass /  0 fail
  level.3   22 pass /  0 fail  (MPI, 4 ranks)
  Total    341 pass / 17 fail   (was 322/35 in February 2026)


CLEANING TEST OUTPUT
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Remove generated output files without touching benchmark reference
files:

  find . -name "*.run" -o -name "*.geo" -o -name "*.stat" \
         -o -name "*.out" | xargs rm -f

Revised: Saman Seifi (Boston University), February 2026
